{
  "texts": [
    "In this case, the recognition accuracy for low-frequency entities created by the BILSTM-CRF algorithm has been improved by 80% and 21.69%, respectively by using the hybrid technique on two entity datasets (MULTIPLE and IDENTIFIER).",
    "Srivastava et al. [106] applied statistical techniques such as CRF and Maximum Entropy (MaxEnt), as well as a rule-based strategy based on a set of language principles by using hybrid technique and Voting techniques are used by the system to increase NER system performance.",
    "The accuracy achieved from rule-based is 96.05% for precision, 91.25% for F1-measure and 86.90% for recall using testing files although accuracy achieved from voting algorithm is 85.51% for precision, 76.62% for recall and 80.82% for F1measure using 40-number of testing files.",
    "Liu et al. [105] discussed a hybrid NER tool for the Urdu script that combines gazetteers, n-gram and rules system using bigram and unigram.",
    "They have generated rules using prefix and suffix characters rather than first and last name lists or potential words on the output list of the n-gram model."
  ]
}